While  clearly  influenced  by Western  bands  like  The  Smashing  Pumpkins, Tool, Dinosaur  Jr., Grimes and The  Cure, ultimately, Kodama reveals  itself  as  Alcest's  'Japanese  album',  drawing  substantial inspiration from Japanese art and culture. Originally  triggered  by  Hayao  Miyazaki's  anime  film Princess  Mononoke, Kodama  picks up  on  the  fate  of  its  protagonist  and,  at  its  core,  deals  with  the  sensation  of  not belonging; of living in between worlds, be it city and nature or the physical and spiritual one.  Duality  is  also  crucial  for  the  visual  approach  of  the  album,  realized  by  French graphic  designer  duo  Førtifem.
